					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355#post-4722199</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355/scp-5932-d#post-4722199</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2020 16:41:39 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ManyMeats</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2104082</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While the dialogue was a bit unpolished, which I am sure will develop at you write more, this was thematically evocative enough that I don't especially care or mind.</p> <p>I do agree with NatVoltaic's point about the Ezriel character feeling like they got the short end of the development stick.</p> <p>Both of those criticisms aside, this is a thorough exploration of the theme in a way that naturally brought out emotion through character interaction rather than blunt force shock. The body horror was good early although some of the &quot;bones protrude&quot; was a bit repetitive in a couple of points.</p> <p>That's a +1 from me.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355#post-4722184</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355/scp-5932-d#post-4722184</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2020 16:13:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Greyve</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4045981</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hey <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2800867&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1595002431" alt="NatVoltaic" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2800867)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/natvoltaic" >NatVoltaic</a></span>, I'm so honored that you decided to read through my skip and consider it &quot;not a bad article&quot;!</p> <p>I totally understand your choice to downvote, and I guess we all have our preferences. I suppose the personal nature of the theme meant that it would naturally not land for some people, and I guess I felt compelled to over-elaborate to make it more accessible. I'm sorry to hear that you consider this &quot;cheesy&quot;, but I'm really glad you think that there's something valuable here.</p> <p>Thanks for your review!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355#post-4721835</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355/scp-5932-d#post-4721835</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 17 Jul 2020 07:59:46 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>NatVoltaic</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2800867</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's a lot of good moments but all of them are interspersed with enough cheesiness that it detracts from the overall experience, and, while this may be a consequence of my own experiences with mental illness and identity, none of the identity themes landed. There was a resonance the first time it was brought up, but the more and more the same messages got repeated the more they got drained value. The character of Ezriel never worked for me, either, since they felt too much like a stock mad scientist with a tragic backstory attached that I couldn't get invested in them. His behavior being tolerated for so long also breaks my suspension of disbelief for what I imagine the Foundation would let fly with their researchers.</p> <p>It's not a bad article, but there's a lot that detracts from it being a truly powerful experience.</p> <p>-1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355#post-4721444</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13552355/scp-5932-d#post-4721444</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 16 Jul 2020 20:32:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>UraniumEmpire</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1613974</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Some of the dialogue can get a bit hokey at points, but it's otherwise really, really good. I enjoyed the somber take on the nature of identity, and felt for the characters all the way through.</p> <p>Sidenote: by the end, &#8230;Like Clockwork by QotSA was playing in my head. Mark of a good piece.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
